==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gauss
<hw>Gauss</hw> <pr>(gous)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after
<person>Karl F. <etsep>Gauss</etsep></person>, a German
mathematician.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>The C.G.S.
unit of density of magnetic field, equal to a field of one line of force
per square centimeter, being thus adopted as an international unit at
Paris in 1900; sometimes used as a unit of intensity of magnetic field.
It was previously suggested as a unit of magnetomotive force.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def><person>Karl F. <etsep>Gauss</etsep></person>, a
German mathematician.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gaussage</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
